<h2>Constellation placement (#1467 / #1566)</h2>
<p>
  Per the conformance contract/impl/binding split: the <strong>contract + vector/golden corpus +
  schema</strong> (incl. the matcher vocabulary) stay <strong>WE</strong>; the <strong>runner / judge
  implementation + the matchers + the run</strong> are <strong>Plateau</strong>; the per-target
  <strong>binding</strong> is the subject, shipped by <strong>FUI</strong>. No new WE→FUI code edge — the
  topology is identical to the webpolicy / webcompliance cascade, and #1282 (WE holds zero executable)
  holds. Each non-engine subsystem still relocates via its own <code>/slice 1294</code> cascade; this
  decision only settles the <em>conformance shape</em> each cascade's binding+corpus slice targets, which
  unblocks them.
</p>

